White Hunter Black Heart [1990]

A thinly fictionalized account of a legendary movie director, whose desire to
hunt down an animal turns into a grim situation with his movie crew in Africa.
The film was based on several Golden Age of Hollywood movie producers. The main
character is based on real-life director John Huston. 

Starring: Clint Eastwood, Jeff Fahey and George Dzundza  
Director: Clint Eastwood
